  "text": "Only when such 'prescription corrections' (the patch to the DCCT protocol) were performed weekly, or more often, did metabolic control consistently meet desired target values. Evidently, when the frequency of such prescription review is relaxed to monthly or quarterly intervals in clinical practice, metabolic control is unlikely to improve [CITATION_1] and, in fact, often degrades.",
